'Eleventh United States Congress' was a meeting of the legislative branch of the
United States federal government, consisting of the United States Senate and the
United States House of Representatives. It met in Washington, D.C. from March 4,
1809 to March 4, 1811, during the first two years of James Madison's presidency.
The apportionment of seats in the House of Representatives was based on the
Second Census of the United States in 1800. Both chambers had a Democratic-
Republican majority.
